title: If the display property of an item is set to 'none', it doesn't take effect in new PDF emitter.
OB: When the display property of an item is set to 'none' in the new PDF emitter, the item is still visible in the generated PDF file.
EB: The display property of an item set to 'none' should hide the item in the generated PDF file.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Open the new PDF emitter.
2. Set the display property of an item to 'none'.
3. Generate a PDF file.
4. Check if the item is still visible in the generated PDF file.
